ity. It concludes with a new interview with Nakhova herself, giving new insight into her creative process and artistic goals. Irina Nakhova: Museum on the Edge provides a vivid look at the work of a visionary artist. Published in partnership with the Zimmerli Museum.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aART / General.2bisacsh  aCollections Catalogs, Exhibitions, individual Artists, Monographs, Russian, Former Soviet Union, soviet union, politics, Arts, music, architecture, Thomas Sokolowski, Julia Tulovsky, Jane Sharp, Natalia Sidlina, Gabriella Ferrari, Irina Nakhova, battle, Art museum, demonstrate, life, memory, moral responsibility, Zimmerli Museum, exploring, art historians, creativity, visionary, partnership.1 aFerrari, Gabriella A.1 aFerrari, Gabriella A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNakhova, Irina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSharp, Jane A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSharp, Jane A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSidlina, Natalia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSidlina, Natalia.1 aSokolowski, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTulovsky, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTulovsky, Julia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2020z9783110704679oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2020 Englishz978311070478508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE CO